# Responsive & Adaptive Design

Reference: `.mba-template/platforms/web-responsive.md`

## Mobile-First Approach

Start with mobile design, enhance for larger screens.

```css
/* Mobile first (default) */
.element {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 16px;
}

/* Tablet */
@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .element {
    width: 50%;
    padding: 24px;
  }
}

/* Desktop */
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .element {
    width: 33.333%;
    padding: 32px;
  }
}
```

## Breakpoints

### Standard (Tailwind-style)
- **sm**: 640px (tablet portrait)
- **md**: 768px (tablet landscape)
- **lg**: 1024px (desktop)
- **xl**: 1280px (large desktop)
- **2xl**: 1536px (extra large)

### Material Design
- **Compact**: 0-599px (phone)
- **Medium**: 600-839px (tablet)
- **Expanded**: 840px+ (desktop)

## Layout Patterns

### Mobile (< 640px)
- Single column
- Full-width components
- Stacked navigation (hamburger)
- Bottom tab bar
- Touch targets: 44px minimum
- Margins: 16px

### Tablet (640-1023px)
- 2-column layouts
- Side navigation appears
- Increased spacing
- Touch targets: 44px
- Margins: 24px

### Desktop (1024px+)
- Multi-column (3-4)
- Persistent side nav
- Hover states
- Click targets: 32px minimum
- Margins: 32-40px
- Max width: 1280-1440px

## Responsive Typography

### Fluid Typography
```css
/* 16px at 320px, 20px at 1440px */
font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.857rem + 0.357vw, 1.25rem);
```

### Scale by Breakpoint
```css
h1 {
  font-size: 2rem; /* 32px mobile */
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem; /* 40px tablet */
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  h1 {
    font-size: 3rem; /* 48px desktop */
  }
}
```

## Grid Systems

### Mobile
- 4-column grid
- 16px gutters
- 16px margins

### Tablet
- 8-column grid
- 16-24px gutters
- 24px margins

### Desktop
- 12-column grid
- 24-32px gutters
- 32-40px margins

## Navigation Patterns

### Mobile
```html
<!-- Hamburger menu -->
<button class="menu-toggle">☰</button>
<nav class="mobile-menu">...</nav>

<!-- Bottom tab bar -->
<nav class="bottom-tabs">
  <a href="#">Home</a>
  <a href="#">Search</a>
  <a href="#">Profile</a>
</nav>
```

### Tablet
```html
<!-- Hybrid: visible items + hamburger -->
<nav class="top-nav">
  <a href="#">Home</a>
  <a href="#">Products</a>
  <button class="menu-toggle">More</button>
</nav>
```

### Desktop
```html
<!-- Full horizontal nav -->
<nav class="top-nav">
  <a href="#">Home</a>
  <a href="#">Products</a>
  <a href="#">About</a>
  <a href="#">Contact</a>
</nav>

<!-- Or persistent sidebar -->
<aside class="sidebar">...</aside>
```

## Responsive Images

### Srcset
```html
<img 
  srcset="image-320w.jpg 320w,
          image-640w.jpg 640w,
          image-1024w.jpg 1024w"
  sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw,
         (max-width: 1024px) 50vw,
         33vw"
  src="image-640w.jpg"
  alt="Description">
```

### Picture Element
```html
<picture>
  <source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="desktop.jpg">
  <source media="(min-width: 640px)" srcset="tablet.jpg">
  <img src="mobile.jpg" alt="Description">
</picture>
```

## Component Adaptations

### Cards
```css
/* Mobile: 1 column */
.card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  gap: 16px;
}

/* Tablet: 2 columns */
@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .card-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
}

/* Desktop: 3-4 columns */
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .card-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 32px;
  }
}
```

### Tables
```css
/* Mobile: Card-based */
@media (max-width: 639px) {
  table, thead, tbody, tr, td {
    display: block;
  }
  
  thead {
    display: none;
  }
  
  tr {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
  }
}

/* Desktop: Standard table */
@media (min-width: 640px) {
  table {
    display: table;
  }
}
```

### Forms
```css
/* Mobile: Full width */
.form-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  gap: 16px;
}

/* Desktop: 2 columns */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .form-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
}
```

## Touch vs Mouse

### Touch Targets
```css
/* Mobile: larger targets */
@media (max-width: 1023px) {
  .button {
    min-height: 44px;
    min-width: 44px;
  }
}

/* Desktop: smaller acceptable */
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .button {
    min-height: 32px;
    min-width: 32px;
  }
}
```

### Hover States
```css
/* Only show hover on devices that support it */
@media (hover: hover) {
  .button:hover {
    background: #0056b3;
  }
}
```

## Container Queries (Modern)

```css
.card-container {
  container-type: inline-size;
}

/* When container is 400px+ */
@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
  }
}
```

## Viewport Units

```css
/* Hero section */
.hero {
  min-height: 60vh; /* 60% of viewport height */
}

/* Full-screen modal */
.modal {
  width: 90vw; /* 90% of viewport width */
  max-width: 600px;
}
```

## Responsive Spacing

```css
/* Fluid spacing */
.section {
  padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
}

/* Breakpoint-based */
.section {
  padding: 32px 16px; /* mobile */
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .section {
    padding: 48px 24px; /* tablet */
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .section {
    padding: 64px 40px; /* desktop */
  }
}
```

## Accessibility

### Zoom Support
- Use relative units (rem, em)
- Test at 200% zoom
- Don't disable user scaling

```html
<!-- Good -->
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

<!-- Bad -->
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, user-scalable=no">
```

### Reduced Motion
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

## Testing

### Devices to Test
- iPhone (375px, 390px, 428px)
- Android (360px, 412px)
- iPad (768px, 1024px)
- Desktop (1280px, 1440px, 1920px)

### Viewport Sizes
- 320px (small mobile)
- 375px (iPhone)
- 768px (tablet portrait)
- 1024px (tablet landscape)
- 1440px (desktop)

## Best Practices

### Do
- Start mobile-first
- Use relative units
- Test on real devices
- Support zoom
- Provide touch targets
- Use responsive images
- Test at breakpoints
- Consider landscape

### Don't
- Design desktop-only
- Use fixed widths
- Disable zoom
- Ignore touch targets
- Use hover-only interactions
- Assume screen size
- Skip mobile testing
- Forget orientation changes
